CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 32, reads: "Auld Lang Syne! - Maxine Sullivan, who swept out of nowhere and caused a nationwide craze with Scottish airs, gets together with some old acquaintances during intermission. Left to right are Lee Smith, Tom Broadus, La Sullivan, Paul French, brother of the famous little lady, and Milton Blount."
TitMainTitle: Maxine Sullivan wearing evening gown and corsage surrounded by, left to right: Lee Smith, Tom Broadus, Paul French, and Milton Blount, Syria Mosque for Night of Stars
